This paper deals with reinforcement learning (RL) algorithms for a specific type of Markov decision process (MDP) called the stochastic action set MDP (SAS-MDP). Therefore, the most likely category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), which is the primary category for RL research. The paper also involves optimization techniques and convergence analysis, which are relevant to categories such as cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.RO (Robotics). The paper's focus on control and decision-making problems suggests that it could also be relevant to cs.SY (Systems and Control) and cs.MA (Multi-Agent Systems).
